  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Executive Summary&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The potential of using the Online Buying Reference Architecture as a basis for the LiUS e-commerce system was assessed.&#xD;
    It was determined that the reference architecture provides a good basis on which to proceed but needs to be enhanced to&#xD;
    support the volumes and performance requirements of the LiUS e-commerce system.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Introduction&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    The purpose of this document is to provide a common understanding of the high-level functional and non-functional&#xD;
    requirements to be supported by the LiUS e-commerce system and to evaluate whether the Online Buying Reference&#xD;
    Architecture could be used as a basis for the LiUS system.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Key Drivers&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    The key business drivers behind the development of the LiUS e-commerce system are:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Complement not replace LiUS stores with the LiUS e-commerce site. Customers should be able to reserve items on-line&#xD;
        and pick them up from stores.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Support effective cross selling (&quot;customers who bought this item also bought these items&quot;).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Provide an e-commerce site in all geographies in which LiUS operates with a single data center.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Significantly improve on the down-time experience by the current site.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Leverage existing product and stock control systems.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Architecture Requirements Checklist&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    The LiUS e-commerce system has the following key functional requirements:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Browsing and searching the site, viewing products and the associated information about those products.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Checking the availability of products at a local LiUS store.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Purchasing products on-line in which case the site visitor must log-on and register if he has not already done so.&#xD;
        The status of orders can then subsequently be checked.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Applying for a LiUS Family card on-line and subsequently checking the status of the application.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Applying for a job at LiUS.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Contacting LiUS to ask a general question or place an e-mail order&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Subscribing to regular updates, news articles etc about LiUS.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &amp;#160;Interfaces to all relevant LiUS back-end systems (currently LiUS Stock Control System, LiUS Product System,,&#xD;
        LiUS e-mail, a search engine and a directory server).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Managing the site content. This includes creating, reviewing and publishing content and managing templates and&#xD;
        product structures. This functionality will be provided by a 3rd party content management system.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Site analysis tools.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Site personalization tools.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Site management tools.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Indexing the site content to allow an external search engine to search that content.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
