&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Statement of Fit&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    The following problems were not addressed by the Online Buying Reference Architecture:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A back-end integration problem was encountered associated with LiUS's requirements for integration with its stock&#xD;
        control system.&amp;#160; Consequently, some modifications will have to be made to the integration server.&amp;#160; The&#xD;
        risk involved is rather limited given that LiUS has considerable experience in back-end integration with various&#xD;
        systems, and it is expected that a large part of the existing adapter design will be reused.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        There is a requirements for the use of e-mail to advise customers of order status.&amp;#160; Although the Online Buying&#xD;
        Reference Architecture provides some support for e-mail, it is not as fully integrated into the transactional&#xD;
        systems as desired.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The requirements is that outbound communications (delivery notes etc) be created using MS-Word, but the Online&#xD;
        Buying Reference Architecture provides a server-based mass-processing document composition paradigm to achieve&#xD;
        performance and integrity.&amp;#160; LiUS has agreed to alter its requirement to fit the recommended pattern.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The performance characteristics required by LiUS, in particular those for peak hour transaction rates, are capable&#xD;
        of being met by the logical reference architecture pattern.&amp;#160; However, currently the physical reference&#xD;
        architecture instantiation described by the Online Buying Reference Architecture proposes use of Distributed Object&#xD;
        Transaction Monitors, which limit the transaction rate to a value below that specified by LiUS.&amp;#160; Additional&#xD;
        architectural work will be needed to modify the current physical reference architecture to support these higher&#xD;
        transaction rates.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
